commitResults.messageTitle: Extract business logic from command parsing
commitResults.messageBody:
Business logic when parsing has been moved into the Lesson class itself,
so that the parser can tell, not ask the Lesson class to initialize it.
This change is also crucial for allowing lessons to be initialized from
classes, independent from the command itself.

As part of Edulog, calendar data (list of lessons) should be stored
along with a list of students. This commit adds the calendar as a new
field to read and store values from.

commitResults.messageTitle: Define JSON formatting for lessons in persistent storage
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit creates a new class to convert lessons to JSON, and JSON to
lessons - ensuring that any changes to the lessons in the calendar are
now persistent.
